climbs.name: What I've Been Missing Out On

content.description:
Climb diagonally  up a ramp that takes small to medium gear.  From here continue up through a water streak, eventually passing through a notch to the top of the route

This route was put up after Brad Young's excellent 2007 guidebook.  For see more newly established routes check out the Mud and Crud site.

mudncrud.com/forums/index.pâ€¦
content.protection: Single rack to 2.5. There is not anchor or bolts at the top. Use good body positioning.
content.location: Located just before  the formation The Lump if you are walking up from Condor Gulch.  Just past the Squareblock look for a small grouping of Pinnacles/boulders on the left side of the trail.  The route is on the larger of the formations on the downhill side.
